Date: Sun, 12 Apr 2026 16:30:00 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 9/9] Cubism SDK first-fetch acceptance dialog + SHA verification

Closes the Phase 3 loose end on Live2D Cubism SDK licensing. The SDK is
proprietary and published under the Live2D Proprietary Software License;
Crow does not bundle or redistribute it. On first pet-mode entry this
patch shows a license-summary dialog and, on accept, fetches the SDK
from Live2D's CDN, verifies its SHA-256, and caches it under
~/.crow/cache/cubism/. Subsequent launches reuse the cached file
without prompting. On cancel or verification failure, pet mode is
disabled for that launch and the web-tiled window stays available.

SDK URL: https://cubism.live2d.com/sdk-web/cubismcore/live2dcubismcore.min.js
SHA-256 pin (Spike 4, Phase 0 report):
  942783587666a3a1bddea93afd349e26f798ed19dcd7a52449d0ae3322fcff7c

Verification is not optional — a mismatch surfaces an error dialog
pointing at Live2D's manual-download page and refuses to load.

Cache layout:
  ~/.crow/cache/cubism/live2dcubismcore.min.js

Applies against: vendor/open-llm-vtuber-web @ d176e7df2366952e3bacbf12cf9a8b18a4315932
(after patches 0001-0005, 0007-0008 — patch 0006 is empty)

